Package: RSDC
Title: Regime-Switching Dynamic Correlation Models
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Authors@R: c(
    person("David", "Ardia", email = "david.ardia.ch@gmail.com", role = "aut"),
    person("Benjamin", "Seguin", email = "benjamin.seguin@outlook.fr", role = c("aut", "cre"))
)
Maintainer: David Ardia <david.ardia.ch@gmail.com>
Description: Estimation, forecasting, simulation, and portfolio construction for 
    regime-switching and constant-correlation models. Supports time-varying 
    transition probabilities (TVTP) via exogenous variables, includes a Hamilton 
    filter implementation, and provides portfolio strategies such as minimum 
    variance and maximum diversification.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
URL: https://github.com/ArdiaD/RegimeSwitchingCorrelation
BugReports: https://github.com/ArdiaD/RegimeSwitchingCorrelation/issues
Imports:
    DEoptim,
    mvtnorm,
    stats,
    utils
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    quadprog,
    Rsolnp
VignetteBuilder: knitr
